### Known compilation issues

| Issue | Resolution |
|-------|-----------|
| Missing copybooks (COBCH0008) | Include `cpy_uncertain` in COBCPY path |
| Illegal level number (COBCH0219) | Remove trailing sequence numbers from data declarations |
| Norwegian characters (Æ Ø Å) garbled | Use ANSI-1252 encoding, not UTF-8 |
| Programs starting with DOH prefix | Skip list — utility programs with special dependencies |

## Local Compile → Server Transfer Workflow

Since the server only has COBOL Server (runtime), compilation happens locally:

```
Developer Machine                              t-no1fkmvct-app
═══════════════════                            ═══════════════════
Visual COBOL (compiler)                        COBOL Server (runtime)
                                               
VCPATH\src\cbl\*.cbl ─► cobol.exe             
                ↓                              
VCPATH\int\*.int  ──┐                          
VCPATH\gs\*.gnt   ──┼── UNC copy ──►          FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Objects\
VCPATH\bnd\*.bnd  ──┘                          FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Objects\bnd\
                                               
Sources\cbl\*.cbl ───── UNC copy ──►           FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Source\cbl\
Sources\cpy\*.cpy ───── UNC copy ──►           FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Source\cpy\
```

**UNC base path:** `\\t-no1fkmvct-app\opt\FkCblApps\FKMVCT\`

The `*_uncertain` source collections are **never** transferred.

### Server directory structure

```
\\t-no1fkmvct-app\opt\FkCblApps\FKMVCT\
├── Objects\              .int and .gnt compiled files (COBPATH points here)
│   └── bnd\              .bnd bind files (optional)
└── Source\
    ├── cbl\              .cbl COBOL source programs (reference + COBDIR)
    └── cpy\              .cpy copybook files (COBCPY points here)
```

