Set by `Configure-VcServerRuntime.ps1` (run once on the server via `/autocur`):

| Variable | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `COBDIR` | `<COBOL Server base>;<OptPath>\FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Objects;<OptPath>\FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Source\cbl` |
| `COBPATH` | `<OptPath>\FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Objects;<OptPath>\FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Source\cbl` |
| `COBCPY` | `<OptPath>\FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Source\cpy;<OptPath>\FkCblApps\FKMVCT\Source\cbl` |
| `COBMODE` | `32` |
| `LIB` | `<COBOL Server base>\lib` |
| `MFVSSW` | `/c /f` |
| `PATH` | includes `<COBOL Server base>\bin`, `lib`, `IBM\SQLLIB\BIN` |

### Pipeline workflow — step tracker

The orchestrator (`Invoke-VcCodeMigration.ps1`) reads `steps-config.json` and iterates steps in config order. Progress is tracked in `current-step.json`. Steps use **x10 numbering** (10, 20, ... 80) to leave gaps for future steps.

```
Step 10–60: AUTOMATIC (run sequentially without stopping)
  Step10  Collect sources (.cbl, .cpy)
  Step15  Resolve uncertain CBL via Ollama AI      ← NEW
  Step20  Check missing copybooks
  Step25  Resolve uncertain CPY via Ollama AI      ← NEW
  Step30  Initialize VC environment
  Step40  Batch compile all programs
  Step50  DB2 bind (.bnd → BASISVCT)
  Step60  Generate migration status report
          ↓
  ══════ PIPELINE PAUSES (ManualRestart) ══════
  Review reports in Reports\ folder
  Rerun script to continue
          ↓
Step 70–80: MANUAL RESTART (pipeline pauses before each)
  Step70  Deploy compiled objects + sources to t-no1fkmvct-app
  Step80  Copy raw sources to server data folder (optional)
```

**Cleanup:** Before each step runs, output from that step and all later steps is deleted.

```powershell
# Full pipeline (starts at Step10, pauses before Step70)
.\DevScripts\Invoke-VcCodeMigration.ps1

# Resume after reviewing reports (continues from paused step)
.\DevScripts\Invoke-VcCodeMigration.ps1

# Force restart from a specific step (cleans output from that step onward)
.\DevScripts\Invoke-VcCodeMigration.ps1 -StartFromStep 40

# Full clean run (deletes current-step.json, starts from Step10)
.\DevScripts\Invoke-VcCodeMigration.ps1 -Fresh

# Quick single-program compile test
.\DevScripts\OneTime\Test-VcSingleCompile.ps1
.\DevScripts\OneTime\Test-VcSingleCompile.ps1 -ProgramName 'GMSTART'

# Server configuration (one-time, via /autocur)
.\ServerScripts\Configure-VcServerRuntime.ps1
.\ServerScripts\Configure-VcServerRuntime.ps1 -DryRun
```

**Adding a new step:** Add an entry to `steps-config.json` with a number between existing steps (e.g. Step15 between 10 and 20), create the script, and add cleanup targets in `Clear-VcStepOutput.ps1`. No orchestrator code changes needed.

